            "answer_text": "99 percent of the time you are fine but that 1 out of 100 time will happen at the worst possible time. Just like getting a flat tire when its pouring down raining when you knew you had a nail stuck in it 5 days ago. It's a good habit to develop because you could pull the USB out as something is being written to it or it could be doing some organizing maintenance function that usually happens in the background or at idle. When you eject the USB from the system you are telling the system OK GUYS! BOSS TELLS ME WE ARE DONE HERE! GRAB YOUR THINGS AND MOVE OUT! ",
